  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Somalia Drought 2016</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Poor post-GU (long rains) exacerbates drought conditions leading to reduced pasture land water shortages and deaths of livestock. This has increased the number of acutely food insecure people to emergency levels with 38% of the Somalia population acutely food insecure and 304 700 children under 5 years of age acutely malnourished. Reports indicate that 4.7 million people are food insecure with an estimated 930 000 already in IPC Phase 3 (crisis) and 22 000 in Phase 4 (emergency). An Emergency Appeal was launched in March 2016. The appeal seeks a total of 1 290 936 Swiss francs to enable IFRC support the Somali Red Crescent Society to deliver assistance and support to 78 990 drought-affected people for 6 months with a focus on the following sectors: health and care water sanitation and hygiene food security nutrition and livelihoods interventions.</narrative>
  </description>
